g removed from my ovary and figured I would provide an update.                           1. They did not allow me to keep the mass and they didn’t give me photos either ☹️ I also lost the right ovary, which we knew was highly likely.                                          2. It was 3lbs, so about 1.3k jelly beans.  3. It is cancerous, they are currently calling it stage 1 ovary cancer.  They’re running a week long test to see what the actual cancer breakdown is and if I’ll have to have chemo and/or other treatments.  4. I am in a lot of pain but the team here is trying to make me as comfortable as possible.                                                        5. I really appreciate all the kind words and thoughts previously! Thank you everyone for your good vibes. If you have any more to spare this week please keep sending them! Hopefully no further treatment needed!                  #forbiddenfruit #donteatit #mango #tumor #cancer #fuckcancer</div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/PKlaeme</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[WorksInHotelDoesntTravel]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>it squirt tiles</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/yB2BV8T</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/hmHafD8.gif" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/yB2BV8T</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[poponthebeezer]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Shame on you, motherfucker.</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/EeQTX3k</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/PMNnvj3.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>Tweet link: https://mobile.twitter.com/theliamnissan/status/1525129489705054211

